trans-unit.source: Provides a regular expression to parse the opening tag of an HTML element, an XML element, or an ASP.NET Web server control tag, for applications that target the .NET Framework 3.5 SP1 and earlier versions.

The <xref:System.Web.RegularExpressions.TagRegex35> class provides a regular expression that ASP.NET uses internally to parse the opening tag of an HTML element, an XML element, or an ASP.NET Web server control tag, for applications that target the [!INCLUDE[net_v35SP1_short](~/includes/net-v35sp1-short-md.md)] and earlier versions.

ASP.NET uses the <xref:System.Web.RegularExpressions.TagRegex?displayProperty=fullName> class for applications that target the [!INCLUDE[net_v40_short](~/includes/net-v40-short-md.md)] and later versions.
The <xref:System.Web.RegularExpressions> classes are used internally by the .NET Framework to parse ASP.NET pages.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.RegularExpressions.TagRegex35"></xref> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.RegularExpressions.TagRegex35"></xref> class with a specified time-out value.

The `A_1` parameter represents the maximum time interval during which the regular expression engine tries to find a match before the operation times out and a <xref:System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexMatchTimeoutException> exception is thrown.
A time-out interval, or <xref href="System.Text.RegularExpressions.Regex.InfiniteMatchTimeout"></xref> if matching operations should not time out.
